\ constant ( value -- ): define an inline word that pushes the value as a
\ literal, so it folds into call sites instead of fetching at run time.

5 constant *softening*
*softening* .  cr
*softening* 3.0 f* .  cr

\ any value works, not just numbers
"abc" constant *tag*
*tag* .  cr

\ inside a compiled word the constant folds to a literal — no call, no fetch
: scale  *softening* 3.0 f* ;
' scale see-compiled
